page.title: 04Ecology - Flora (A)
page.content:
There is a large variety of wild flowers and grasses found in this area as follows: {Seashore and Marshland} scurvy grass, sea bladder campion, thrift, sea bindweed, sea plantain, silverweed, sea aster, water celery, sea purslane, sea campion, orache, sea milkwort, bog bedstraw, birdseye primrose, bogbean, yellow flagins, watercress, globeflower, brooklime, water fennel, butterwort, marsh orchid, water avens, lousewort, golden saxifrage, water crowfoot, sweet cicily, pyramidal bugle, marsh valerian.
{Limestone Terrain} yellow rattle, lambs lettuce, bell heather, heartsease, early purple orchid, crosswort, moschatel....{cont.
